headline: Citi says a ‘supermajors super-cycle’ is coming for U.S. airlines
summary: Investing.com -- Citi analyst John Godyn said in a note Thursday that the U.S. airline industry is heading into what they call a “Supermajors Super-Cycle,” arguing that 2026 will mark the start of an elongated mid-cycle in which the largest network carriers outperform the rest of the sector.

headline: Review & Preview: Gaming Out the Fed
summary: The closer we get to the next Federal Reserve meeting, the more confident investors seem to be about another rate cut—and the higher stocks go.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average added 408 points or 0.9%.  Better known as the Dow Transports and made up of 20 transportation stocks—including UPS, FedEx, J.B. Hunt, Delta Air Lines, and Uber Technologies—the index is up eight consecutive trading days, its longest winning streak since October 2021.
